      "text": [
        " رَجُلٍ نَسِيَ أَنْ يَذْبَحَ بِمِنًى حَتَّى زَارَ اَلْبَيْتَ فَاشْتَرَى بِمَكَّةَ ثُمَّ نَحَرَهَا قَالَ «لاَ بَأْسَ قَدْ أَجْزَأَ عَنْهُ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3092 - Muawiyah ibn Ammar narrated from Abu Abdullah (as) regarding a man who forgot to slaughter in Mina until he visited the Kaaba, then purchased an animal in Mecca and slaughtered it.\nImam (as) said: \"There is no harm; it suffices for him.\""
        ]
      }
